  There are new surveillance and detention policies, such as the sweeping USA Patriot Act.  In the words of Nat Hentoff, \'93never in the history of the First Amendment has any suppression of speech been so sweeping and difficult to contest as this one,
\'94 which allows the FBI to \'93demand from bookstores and libraries the names of books bought or borrowed by anyone suspected of involvement in \lquote international terrorism\rquote  or \lquote clandestine activities.\rquote \'94}{\fs24\super \chftn 
