\par My own response to shock and speechlessness in New York City was the opposite\emdash to need, desperately, for language to be pushed outward or inward\emdash to change and be changed, to be charged, remade.  What might }{\i\fs24 that}{\fs24 
 new poetry look like?  What sources might it look back to?  And who will be its readers?
